<h1 class="title">FISTICUFFS</h1>
<nav class="outer">
  <form class="inner" action="/">
    <input type="submit" value="Home">
  </form>
  <form class="inner" action="/instructions">
    <input type="submit" value="Instructions">
  </form>
  <form class="inner" action="/profiles/<%=session[:user]["id"]%>">
    <input type="submit" value="Profile">
  </form>
  <form class="inner" action="/<%=session[:user]["id"]%>/matches">
    <input type="submit" value="Matches">
  </form>
  <form class="inner" action="/logout" method='get'>
    <input type="hidden" name='_method' value='delete'>
    <input type="submit" value='Log-Out'>
  </form>  
  <%if @unseen.count > 0%>
  <h6>You have new matches</h6>
  <%end%>
  <%if @unread.count > 0%>
  <h6>You have new messages</h6>
  <%end%>
</nav>
<div id="instructions">
<h2>How to Use Fisticuffs</h2>
 The purpose of Fisticuffs is to bring people together in the name of honorable combat.
  <br>
  After signing up, via Facebook, click on Profile and add your height and weight.
  <br>
  Say a little something about yourself in the Bio field.
  <br>
  On the main page, you'll see another like-minded user.
  <br>
  Click "Let's Fight" if the user is something you'd like to engage in battle with.
  <br>
  Click "No Thanks" if you'd prefer not to.
  <br>
  Alternatively, use the left and right arrows on your keyboard to choose who you'd like to fight, 
  <br>
  left and right being "No Thanks" and "Let's Fight," respectively.
  <br>
  </div>